<span id="freeTextContainer14944915794660687713">I&apos;ve got a vague memory reading these short stories as a kid, a quick Google search also revealed an early 90&apos;s BBC animated series which looked familiar and probably the reason for owning thr book.<br/><br/>Out of the 12 stories in the collection, my favourites were the ones that I had the strongest recollections.<br/>Like how the workshy Camel got his hump and a baby Elephant developt a trunk.<br/>These stories are so quirky and memorable!<br/><br/>Coincidentally the strongest stories are in the first half of the collectio</span>
  <span id="freeText14944915794660687713" style="display:none">I've got a vague memory reading these short stories as a kid, a quick Google search also revealed an early 90's BBC animated series which looked familiar and probably the reason for owning thr book.<br /><br />Out of the 12 stories in the collection, my favourites were the ones that I had the strongest recollections.<br />Like how the workshy Camel got his hump and a baby Elephant developt a trunk.<br />These stories are so quirky and memorable!<br /><br />Coincidentally the strongest stories are in the first half of the collection as the others introduce humans into the tales and explains how both drawings and the alphabet was created.<br /><br />It's always fun to have that 'oh I remember this one now' moment, whilst also being perfect length to read as bedtime stories.<br />It was fun revisiting them!</span>
